<F P=100> Peru </F>
<H3> <TI>   State of Emergency Declared in La Mar, Kimbiri </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    State of Emergency Declared in La Mar, Kimbiri </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY2604225694 Lima EL COMERCIO in Spanish 16 Apr 94 Political 
Section p A7 </F>

<F P=103> PY2604225694 </F>
<F P=104>  Lima EL COMERCIO </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Yesterday, the government declared a state of 
emergency in La Mar Province (Ayacucho Department) and in the 
neighboring Kimbiri district (located in Quillabamba Province, 
Cuzco Department) to expedite operations that the Armed Forces 
Joint Command is conducting in the area against terrorism and 
drug trafficking. According to a supreme decree published 
yesterday in the official newspaper, constitutional rights in 
the area will be suspended for 60 days. 
  The same edition reports that the state of emergency has 
been 
extended for 60 days in Pasco Department and in the provinces of 
Huancayo, Concepcion, Jauja, Satipo, and Chanchamayo (Junin 
Department); in Castrovirreina, Huancavelica, and Huaytara 
Provinces (Huancavelica Department); and in Cangallo, Lucanas, 
and Huamanga Provinces (Ayacucho Department). 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

