<F P=100> CARIBBEAN </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Labor Activities Suspended 2 May for Holiday </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Labor Activities Suspended 2 May for Holiday </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL2604210394 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 1930 GMT 
26 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2604210394 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] According to Article 86 of the Labor Code, the 
Ministry of Labor and Social Security has decided to transfer 
the 1 May holiday, which falls on a Sunday, to Monday, 2 May. 
  The suspension of labor activities on Monday will be in 
effect except for those that relate to harvest and other urgent 
agricultural and livestock production activities, 
continuous-production industries, and urgencies in the the 
port-transport-internal economy network. 
  Likewise not included in this labor holiday are services 
related to transport, hospitals, funerals, pharmacies, on-duty 
gasoline stations, gardens, recreation centers, radio and 
television broadcasting, tourist attractions, and collection and 
distribution of milk. 
  The Ministry of Domestic Trade will establish the opening 
and 
closing hours for the domestic trade system. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

