<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Delegations from Italy, Venezuela, Mexico, Puerto 
Rico, Japan, Cyprus, and Greece have arrived in Cuba to 
participate in the May Day ceremonies. There are over 250 
invited guests already in Cuba; they are currently visiting 
Havana work centers and participating in May Day ceremonies at 
unions and workplaces. The international relations department of 
the Cuban Workers Federation added that the visitors represent 
over 15 countries and 34 unions and organizations of various 
leanings. 
  The arrival in Cuba of union delegates from the United 
States, Pakistan, and the Vasque region is expected tonight. 
They will participate in the May Day ceremonies scheduled for 30 
April in Matanzas, Pinar del Rio, Havana Province, and four 
Havana municipalities, as well as in the National Assembly of 
the People's Government session being held in honor of May Day. 

