<H3> <TI>   Yadira Garcia Reviews 1 May Matanzas Plans </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yadira Garcia Reviews 1 May Matanzas Plans </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL2704155694 Havana Radio Progreso Network in Spanish 1100 
GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2704155694 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Progreso Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Matanzas Province correspondent Candido Dominguez </F>
-- live or recorded] 
  [Text] Approximately 70,000 people here will participate in 
the parade commemorating international workers day, which will 
take place next Saturday [30 April] at 0900 on the Matanzas Bay 
viaduct. The spaciousness of this new avenue that skirts the 
bay, along with the care with which the preparations are being 
made, portend a special splendor to this massive gesture, 
despite the fact that the inevitable austerity of the current 
moment prevents our using certain equipment and other material 
resources. 
  Yadira Garcia, a member of the Politburo and first secretary 
of the Communist Party of Cuba in Matanzas, said that the people 
of Matanzas have the special responsibility this year of 
expressing the joy, militancy, and steadfastness not only of the 
people of the province, but of all the people throughout the 
nation. Making the closing speech today [date not specified] at 
a meeting to review preparations for the 1 May activity, Garcia 
recalled that this year there will be parades only in Matanzas 
and Pinar del Rio. She expressed her confidence that the parade 
to be held in the City of Matanzas will be a success, and 
announced that over 100 foreign guests will attend. 
  This meeting, held at the Atenas movie theater, was attended 
by administrative and union representatives from all sectors, 
the UJC [Union of Young Communists], and the mass organizations, 
and was characterized by great enthusiasm, expressed in 
exchanges of emulative challenges between unions. 

</TEXT>

