<H3> <TI>   Tampering With Mail Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Tampering With Mail Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   94P20684A </F>
<F P=103> 94P20684A </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
CSO 

    [Editorial Report] Havana TRABAJADORES in Spanish of 11 
April 1994 on page 2 reports that, at a meeting of the National 
Committee of the Communications Workers Union, members discussed 
crimes committed by workers and problems affecting the telephone 
sector related to transportation and fuel shortages. Agustin 
Lopez, secretary general of the union, acknowledged reports of 
tampering with international mail and deliveries of newspapers 
to the provinces. Lopez attributed the crimes to inattention by 
administrators and the unions. General Colas Sanchez stated: "It 
is essential that all honest communications workers combat the 
criminal acts taking place in their sector." 

</TEXT>

