<H3> <TI>   Cavallo Says U.S. Will Not Apply Sanctions </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cavallo Says U.S. Will Not Apply Sanctions </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY2804181894 Buenos Aires Radio Nacional Network in Spanish 
1600 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY2804181894 </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires Radio Nacional Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Economy Minister Domingo Cavallo, who returned today 
from Washington, stated that the United States will not apply 
sanctions against Argentina over the Patents Law, which has not 
yet been approved by Congress. 
  Cavallo also maintained that during his negotiations with 
U.S. businessmen, bankers, and government officials, the matter 
of the Patents Law did not come up. 

</TEXT>

