<F P=100> Guatemala </F>
<H3> <TI>   Court Approves 14 Aug Elections </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Court Approves 14 Aug Elections </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2904004094 Panama City ACAN in Spanish 2348 GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA2904004094 </F>
<F P=104>  Panama City ACAN </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Guatemala City, 27 Apr (ACAN-EFE) -- The 
Constitutionality Court (CC) reported today that the country's 
new Congress will be elected on 14 August, just as had been 
established by the Supreme Electoral Tribunal (TSE). 
  The CC turned down the temporary amparo granted by the 
Supreme Court of Justice (CSJ) to Deputy Carlos Arroyave against 
the TSE, whom he accused of violating his rights by calling 
parliamentary elections for 14 August. According to the 
resolution issued today, the CC turned down the amparo granted 
by the CSJ on 22 April because it considers the situation 
presented by Solidarity Action Movement Deputy Arroyave as 
"nonexistent." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

