<F P=100> Nicaragua </F>
<H3> <TI>   Replacement Chosen for General Ortega </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Replacement Chosen for General Ortega </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2804194194 Managua Radio Corporacion in Spanish 1330 GMT 
28 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2804194194 </F>
<F P=104>  Managua Radio Corporacion </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Trench" newscast] </F>
  [Text] General Humberto Ortega's replacement is ready. 
Sources close to the Presidential House have learned Major Gen. 
Joaquin Cuadra Lacayo will be promoted to lieutenant general of 
the Sandinist Army. He will be the highest-ranking officer in 
the country, second only to the general [Humberto Ortega], of 
course, who does not allow anyone to be his equal. 
  Sources very close to the Presidential House have leaked 
that 
President Violeta Barrios will announce, any moment now, the 
promotion of Major Gen. Joaquin Cuadra Lacayo to lieutenant 
general. Mrs. Barrios, as supreme commander of the Armed Forces 
and defense minister, has the constitutional power to grant this 
promotion, thus making Cuadra Lacayo the second highest-ranking 
officer, second to Humberto Ortega, who does not allow any 
officer to become his equal; that would be disrespectful. 
  It is believed this appointment represents a message to the 
U.S. Government about the changes Mrs. Barrios is making to the 
image of her country and government. Many see this as a maneuver 
that is taking place with the concurrence of Humberto Ortega, of 
course, who has just said at the Olof Palme Convention Center 
that anyone trying to change the correlation of forces would 
provoke further destabilization, which could lead to a new 
Nicaraguan civil war. 

</TEXT>

