<H3> <TI>   Roundup of Economic Reports </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Roundup of Economic Reports </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY2804164494 </F>
<F P=103> PY2804164494 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
BFN 

    [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on economic activities in Peru monitored through 21 
April. 
  The Eximbank of Japan on 13 April reported in Tokyo that it 
will grant $22.5 million to Peru to finance electricity 
projects. The agreement was signed during the Inter-American 
Development Bank annual meeting held in Guadalajara, Mexico. 
(Lima LA REPUBLICA in Spanish 14 Apr 94 p 2) 
  The Lima stock market showed an increase of 24.3 percent in 
the year's first three months, when it traded $948 million 
compared with the $253.1 million negotiated in the same period 
in 1993. (Lima EL COMERCIO in Spanish 17 Apr 94 p A16) 
  The State Petroleum Agency reported that the new oil well in 
the Pavayacu oil field, 235 km west of Iquitos, will begin 
operation on 19 April. It will produce 6,000 barrels of oil 
daily. Oil production went from 1,500 barrels per day in 
February 1993 to 14,885 barrels in March following the discovery 
of 11 oil wells in the past 12 months. (Lima EL COMERCIO in 
Spanish 18 Apr 94 p 1) 

</TEXT>

