<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Judicial Cooperation Accord Signed With Pakistan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Judicial Cooperation Accord Signed With Pakistan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC3003063194 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in 
Arabic 1230 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC3003063194 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Egypt and Pakistan signed a judicial cooperation 
agreement today. The agreement provides for extraditing 
criminals and terrorists and individuals implicated in illegal 
dealing in weapons and explosives. Justice Minister Counselor 
Faruq Sayf-al-Nasr and his Pakistani counterpart Iqbal Haidar 
signed the agreement. 
  Sayf-al-Nasr affirmed that Pakistan, like all other Islamic 
states, condemns terrorism in every form. He noted that the 
agreement they initialed aims to fight crime and guarantee 
respect for human rights. The final signing will take place in 
Islamabad soon. 
  The Pakistani justice minister commended the Justice 
Ministry's efforts to conclude the agreement. He noted that the 
Pakistani Government is willing to enforce its articles as of 
today if the Egyptian Government can specify the names of 
terrorists who have escaped to Pakistan so that they can be 
handed over like any other criminal. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-11633 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drnes062_c_94004" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-NES-94-062 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  30 Mar 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Final Signing in 10 Days </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Final Signing in 10 Days </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC3003145094 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in 
Arabic 1230 GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC3003145094 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Interior Minister Hasan al-Alfi has said that the 
security services have successfully brought back 29 wanted 
terrorists from abroad. Egypt and Pakistan are fully 
cooperating and exchanging information in this regard, al-Alfi 
said. An agreement between Egypt and Pakistan on the 
extradition of criminals and terrorists will be signed in 
Islamabad in 10 days, al-Alfi noted. 
  The interior minister said that the state welcomes any 
terrorist who listens to reason and it promises to protect 
repenting terrorists and their families. He called on the 
extremists to return to the true path of God, for their sake and 
that of their country. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

