<H3> <TI>   Cairo Talks Stall, Resume; Agreement Announced </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cairo Talks Stall, Resume; Agreement Announced </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Security Agreement Further Detailed </H4>

<F P=102> TA3103054894 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0500 GMT 31 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA3103054894 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] An Israel-PLO agreement on security arrangements in 
Hebron, to be signed by the delegation heads this morning, was 
reached in Cairo past midnight last night. Our correspondent in 
Cairo Arye Gus reports that under the agreement, an increased 
international force will be deployed in Hebron in exchange for 
the Palestinian consent to waive their demand for Palestinian 
police there. 
  PLO officials said that about 160 observers from three 
countries -- Norway, Denmark, and Italy -- will be stationed in 
Hebron, and as said, there will be no Palestinian police there. 
  The agreement has paved the way for the resumption of the 
Gaza and Jericho autonomy talks and for an early deployment of a 
Palestinian police force in Gaza. 

</TEXT>

