<H3> <TI>   Cairo Talks Stall, Resume; Agreement Announced </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cairo Talks Stall, Resume; Agreement Announced </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Sides Give Accord `Final Going Over' </H4>

<F P=102> NC3103095494 Paris AFP in English 0940 GMT 31 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC3103095494 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, March 31 (AFP)--Israel and PLO put the final 
touches to a security agreement for the West Bank town of Hebron 
on Thursday before a scheduled signing ceremony, PLO spokesman 
Usamah Sharab said. 
  Israeli deputy chief of staff, General Amnon Shahaq, and PLO 
chief negotiator Nabil Sha'th were to sign the agreement. 
  "The two delegations are giving the text a final going 
over," 
he said. 
  Both sides had asked for slight changes to be made, a source 
close to the negotiators said. 
  The accord calls for the deployment of 160 international 
observers in Hebron, where a Jewish settler killed 30 
Palestinian worshippers on February 25. 

</TEXT>

