<H3> <TI>   Fatah: Jabalyah Killings To Affect Negotiations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fatah: Jabalyah Killings To Affect Negotiations </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN3003201794 Baghdad Voice of the PLO in Arabic 1700 GMT 30 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN3003201794 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad Voice of the PLO </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Palestine National Liberation Movement, Fatah, 
has asserted that the Jabalyah camp massacre is a premeditated 
murder meant to liquidate Fatah elements. 
  In a statement distributed in the occupied territories 
yesterday, the Fatah Movement added: This new massacre will 
negatively affect the course of the negotiations. 
  The Fatah Movement held the Israeli Government and the 
Israeli military establishment responsible for the massacres 
committed against our people. It reiterated that the six 
Palestinian victims were deliberately killed by the bullets of 
the terrorist Israeli undercover units. 

