<H3> <TI>   Passports To Take on New `Security Aspect' 1 Apr </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Passports To Take on New `Security Aspect' 1 Apr </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2903060494 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 0430 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2903060494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Foreign Ministry's Information and Press 
Department has reported that ordinary, diplomatic, and service 
passports will change. So that passports are in line with the 
objectives and values of the Islamic Republic of Iran's system, 
as of 1 April, the anniversary of the establishment of the 
Islamic Republic of Iran, new passports will replace the current 
ones. The new passports will be different in size, shape, and 
in their security aspect from the existing documents and will be 
compiled by a computer in a way that will facilitate access to 
information and to references. 

</TEXT>

