<F P=100> Libya </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Clarification' Issued on Oppositions' London Meeting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Clarification' Issued on Oppositions' London Meeting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2803105694 London AL-HAYAH in Arabic 26 Mar 94 p 4 </F>
<F P=103> PM2803105694 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-HAYAH </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Clarification on Libyan Opposition's </F>
London Meeting"] 
  [Text] London, AL-HAYAH -- Clarifying a report published by 
AL-HAYAH last Wednesday on Libyan oppositionists' London 
meeting, Prince Muhammad al-Hasan al-Rida al-Sanusi has said: 
  1. We renew our respect for all Libyan opposition figures 
and groups and wish them success in ridding the country of its 
predicament. We also renew our willingness and desire to 
meeting with any figure or group to exchange views on the Libyan 
problem. We stress that we do not consider ourselves an 
opposition faction or organization. We belong to everyone, in 
accordance with the traditions of our al-Sanusi family, which 
has never sided with one group against another. 
  2. With regard to the meeting held in the London house of a 
figure known for his generosity and good reputation, we clarify 
that it was not a political meeting. It was an invitation to a 
lunch which witnessed general and unspecific discussions about 
Libyan issues, just like any other discussions one would expect 
at such meetings. No memorandum was written, nor were 
signatures on any initiative collected. 
  3. We have been surprised by what was published and 
circulated by Libyan brothers. We had organized the issues 
raised at the meeting. We would like to stress that we are not 
against any opportunity to discuss current political affairs, 
but we prefer that there be clear prior organization for the 
sake of the unity of all the nation's sons. 
  4. We do not wish to be a means for any plan or a tool for 
any quarter seeking to achieve personal or factional interests. 
And we assure everyone that we will respect the will of every 
person and quarter and will not interfere in the Libyan 
opposition's affairs. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

