<H3> <TI>   Buwayz Links Church Bombing to Hebron Massacre </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Buwayz Links Church Bombing to Hebron Massacre </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0104070494 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0610 GMT 1 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0104070494 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 1 Apr (MENA)--Lebanese Foreign Minister Faris 
Buwayz has stressed that the bombing of the Sayyidat al-Najat 
Church was committed after the al-Ibrahimi Mosque massacre to 
divert international attention away from the massacre. 
  In an interview with the newspaper AL-AHRAM published today, 
the Lebanese foreign minister said that a number of people have 
been arrested for the church bombing. These people revealed 
that they has connections to Israeli officers and had obtained 
instructions, funds, and equipment that enabled them to assemble 
the explosive device, Buwayz added. 
  Buwayz maintained that it is not possible to terminate the 
resistance before obtaining assurances that south Lebanon will 
return to Lebanon because the resistance is not the reason for 
the Israeli occupation but a result of it. 
  Responding to a question on the Middle East market, the 
Lebanese foreign minister said: Any concept of future regional 
relations must be based on the dimensions of peace. 

</TEXT>

