<H3> <TI>   First Palestinian Police To Enter Gaza 5 Apr </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    First Palestinian Police To Enter Gaza 5 Apr </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0104053994 Cairo MENA in Arabic 2255 GMT 31 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0104053994 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 31 Mar (MENA)--Responsible Palestinian 
sources have told MENA that the first group of Palestinian 
police will arrive in the Gaza Strip on Tuesday [5 April] in 
accordance with the agreement reached today during negotiations 
between the Palestinian and the Israeli delegations in Cairo. 
  The same sources said that this group will be followed by a 
larger group on Thursday. The sources pointed out that during 
the talks held today a detailed agreement was reached on the 
agenda for the Gaza-Jericho negotiations, which will resume in 
Cairo on Sunday. [Word indistinct] the time schedule for the 
entry of the Palestinian police force to Gaza and Jericho. 
  In another development, Dr. Nabil Sha'th, Palestinian 
President Yasir 'Arafat's political adviser and head of the 
Palestinian negotiating team, stated that the implementation of 
all measures in the Declaration of Principles will be acted on 
quickly. 
  MENA has learned that this evening Dr. Sha'th went to the 
Norwegian Embassy in Cairo and submitted an official request 
that international observers be sent to Hebron City to begin 
carrying out their duties there as soon as possible. 

</TEXT>

