<H3> <TI>   Russia Said Ready To Help Hebron Protection Force </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russia Said Ready To Help Hebron Protection Force </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN3103210194 Sanaa Voice of Palestine in Arabic 1800 GMT 31 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN3103210194 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Voice of Palestine </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brother President Abu-'Ammar [Yasir 'Arafat], 
president of the state of Palestine and chairman of the PLO 
Executive Committee, has received information that Russia is 
ready to take part in an international force to protect 
Palestinian citizens in Hebron. The Palestinian News Agency 
says that this decision by the Russian leadership has been 
emphasized in a letter conveyed by the Russian ambassador in 
Tunis to brother President Abu-'Ammar. 
  Meanwhile, President Abu-'Ammar has asked France to help 
provide an international protection for the Palestinian citizens 
in the occupied territories. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

