<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fresh Offensives Reported in South; Many Homeless </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fresh Offensives Reported in South; Many Homeless </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3103123994 Tehran IRNA in English 1125 GMT 31 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD3103123994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Gonaveh (Bushehr), March 31, IRNA -- Scores of Iraqi 
families have been made homeless as a result of the Iraqi 
regime's fresh offensives on the southern marshlands, reported 
reliable sources here today. 
  According to the fresh arrivals, the people in the Iraqi 
marshlands especially the women and children, are suffering 
through shortage of foodstuffs and medicine. 
  The radio "Voice of Iraqi People," operating from somewhere 
inside Iraq, reported today that scores of refuge families in 
al-Basrah, Nasiriyah and al-Amarah have left their homes for 
safe havens, near the Iranian borders in the southeast. 
  The Iraqi Arabs betrayed by the U.S. and its coalition 
forces 
which incited them against Saddam Husayn and then deserted them 
in the aftermath of the Persian Gulf war in 1991, have been 
subject to rigorous economic sanctions. 
  The Iraqi regime launches periodical attacks on the 
southerners and other opponents in the central and northern 
parts. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-11777 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drnes063_k_94006" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-NES-94-063 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  31 Mar 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Syria's Khaddam Receives Kurdish Envoy </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Syria's Khaddam Receives Kurdish Envoy </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN3103200794 (Clandestine) Voice of Iraqi Kurdistan in 
Arabic 1530 GMT 31 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN3103200794 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of Iraqi Kurdistan </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On 29 March, Syrian Vice President 'Abd-al-Halim 
Khaddam received in his office in Damascus 'Ali al-Sanjari, 
member of the Kurdistan Democratic Party political bureau and 
the party's Arab Affairs official. During their meeting, they 
discussed the general situation in Iraq, with a particular 
emphasis on Kurdistan, as well as the recent Iraqi regime's 
threats. 
  Both sides expressed the desire to strengthen relations 
between our party and the Arab Socialist Ba'th Party in Syria. 
  Khaddam conveyed greetings from President Hafiz al-Asad to 
brother struggler Mas'ud Barzani and thanked him for sending a 
special envoy from the party leadership to take part in a prayer 
meeting for the soul of deceased Basil al-Asad. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

