<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   More on Soldiers' Disobeying Order </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    More on Soldiers' Disobeying Order </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA3103154394 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1400 GMT 31 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA3103154394 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The National Religious Party [NRP] Knesset faction 
is against soldiers' disobeying orders, and says that the IDF 
[Israel Defense Forces] -- including all its forces and echelons 
-- is above the public debate. Our correspondent Hayim Hecht 
reports the decision was made unanimously following a session 
lasting more than four hours. The NRP faction also states that 
a government decision to evacuate Jews from their homes and 
lands in Eretz Yisra'el is a terrible edict which contradicts 
Zionism, Jewish law, and human ethics. The NRP promises to do 
everything within its power to foil such a decision and calls on 
the entire Israeli public to evince passive, nonviolent civil 
resistance to foil such a decision, if it is made. 

</TEXT>

