<H3> <TI>   Right-Wing Support Rally for Hebron in Qiryat Arba' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Right-Wing Support Rally for Hebron in Qiryat Arba' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA3103172194 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1500 GMT 31 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA3103172194 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A support rally for the Jewish settlers in Hebron 
and Qiryat Arba' ended in Qiryat Arba' a short time ago. Our 
correspondent Gil Litman reports that many thousands of people 
participated in the rally, among them the heads of the Knesset 
opposition factions and Knesset members [MK's]. The organizers 
distributed registration cards urging participants to defend 
Hebron if a decision is taken to evacuate Jews from the city. 
Border policemen prevented several young Kakh supporters from 
hoisting Kakh flags during the rally. 
  [Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1600 GMT 31 March, 
reporting on the Qiryat Arba' rally, adds the following: "MK 
Ari'el Sharon, who addressed the massive rally, said that as far 
as he is concerned, Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres is no longer 
the foreign minister of the Jewish state, but rather the foreign 
minister of the state of Palestine. According to Sharon the 
Israeli Government is not a Jewish and Zionist government, and 
as far as he is concerned, Shim'on Peres -- who is returning the 
Gaza Strip and Jericho to 'Arafat -- can stay there with the 
head of the PLO." "MK Binyamin Netanyahu called on the audience 
to oppose the evacuation of Jews from Hebron by all legal means 
possible. MK Refa'el Eytan demanded that the government hold 
elections prior to such a move."] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

