<H3> <TI>   Poll Shows Majority Opposes Hebron Evacuation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Poll Shows Majority Opposes Hebron Evacuation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2503203994 Tel Aviv YEDI'OT AHARONOT in Hebrew 25 Mar 94 p 
4 </F>

<F P=103> TA2503203994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv YEDI'OT AHARONOT </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [YEDI'OT AHARONOT poll conducted by the Dahaf Institute </F>
headed by Dr. Mena Tzemah] 
  [Text] Should or should not the settlers be evacuated from 
the town of Hebron? 
  Should be evacuated -- 35 percent; should not be evacuated 
-- 
60 percent; did not answer -- 5 percent. 
  Should or should not the government agree to the stationing 
of an armed international force in the territories? 
  Should agree -- 35 percent; should not agree -- 60 percent; 
did not answer -- 5 percent. 
  The poll which was conducted on Tuesday and Wednesday this 
past week encompassed 503 interviewees constituting a 
representative sample of the entire adult population in Israel. 
Maximal poll error is 4 percent. 

</TEXT>

