<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister Urges Lifting Embargo </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Minister Urges Lifting Embargo </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0104115994 Baghdad INA in Arabic 1100 GMT 1 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN0104115994 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 1 Apr (INA) -- Foreign Minister Muhammad 
Sa'id al-Sahhaf has said Iraq has fulfilled its international 
obligations, particularly Resolution 687, which stipulates, in 
return, that the Security Council should immediately lift the 
Iraq embargo in line with Paragraph 22. 
  In an interview with Egyptian television screened last 
night, 
al-Sahhaf said it is the right of the Iraqi people and 
government, in line with international law, to take measures 
that keep them alive and ensures their future if pressure on the 
Security Council persists in order to prevent the lifting of the 
embargo. 
  He said lifting the Iraq embargo is necessary and is 
stipulated by Resolution 687, Paragraph 22, and that any talk to 
the contrary is obvious manipulation of the resolutions and 
their contents. 
  Regarding the allegations of the Kuwaiti regime about 
missing 
persons, the foreign minister said Iraq had cooperated with 
three envoys sent by the Arab League, the Security Council, and 
the International Committee of the Red Cross, and that Iraq 
holds no Kuwaiti people at all. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

