Daily Report 
<DATE1>  31 Mar 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Device Explodes in al-Jizah Governorate </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Device Explodes in al-Jizah Governorate </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC3103112494 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1057 GMT 31 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC3103112494 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 31 Mar (MENA)--A locally made explosive 
device planted by an unidentified man under a car parked outside 
the International Trade Bank near the al-Zamalik Club fence on 
Jami'at al-Dual al-'Arabiyah Street in the al-Muhandisin 
neighborhood of al-Jizah went off this morning. The explosion 
caused no casualties but damaged four cars. The bank's windows 
were also shattered. 
  Al-Jizah security officials, explosives and other experts, 
and criminal laboratory experts went to investigate the incident. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>
